<font color="#FF0000">PTSD</font><br>
<tt>Tue Jan  9 22:16:14 US/Eastern 2001
</tt><p>
I have never talked to anyone who has had PTSD or known anyone with it so I don't know too much about the subject. I do think that a sever strain on ones body and mind can do weird things to your chemical make-up. I think that PTSD is a real thing and can happen to people who go to war and might experience overwhelmingly tramatic events. I don't, however, believe that it is hereditary or that it can pass from one generation to the next. Like someone said before on the subject, the child my pick up some characterists of PTSD from it's parent but I don't think it is really the same as having it. They never went through the stress and never had the strain put on them.<br><br>
~Chris~ 
